President Muhammadu Buhari has returned back to the country on Friday, following his trip to Kenya for the United Nations Environmental Programme. This was disclosed in a statement by Buhari’s aide, Buhari Sallau, stating that the president is currently in Abuja. “President Muhammadu Buhari has returned to Abuja, after his participation in the 50th Anniversary of the UN Environmental Programme in Nairobi, Kenya,” the statement partly read. JUST IN: Buhari Will Still Return To UK For Medical Check-Up,… MASSOB Accuses FG Of Killing Pro-Biafra Leaders To Provoke Civil… Recall that in an earlier a statement by Femi Adesina, the Special Adviser, Media and Publicity to the President, on March 1, Buhari was supposed to spend two weeks in UK for a medical check-up. “From Kenya, President Buhari will proceed to London for routine medical checks that will last for a maximum of two weeks,” Adesina said.